laboratory_examinations.findings: Prior to the injection of liquid barium, an appropriately positioned gastric band was noted. The patient ingested a small cup of thin liquid barium which passed freely across the gastric band. There is no evidence of associated prolapse, malpositioned band, or other obstruction.

laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: Laboratory examination for leukocytes and microorganisms
laboratory_examinations.findings: NO POLYMORPHONUCLEAR LEUKOCYTES SEEN. NO MICROORGANISMS SEEN.
